title: John Rowe's college football picks for Oct. 17 - College Football
text:
Rowe’s picks 
*Notre Dame (-6 1/2) over USC — Hard to figure how USC’s players will react to the coaching mess.
Michigan State (+7 1/2) against *Michigan — The Spartans’ offense will test Michigan’s improved defense.
*Iowa State (+20 1/2) against TCU — The Horned Frogs have won their last three road games by a total of 16 points.
Play of the day 
*LSU (-7) over Florida — As well as Florida’s defense has played, it hasn’t seen the likes of Leonard Fournette.
Other games 
Alabama (-3 1/2) over *Texas A&M; *Northwestern (+2) against Iowa; Penn State (+18 1/2) against *Ohio State; Oklahoma (-4) over *Kansas State
*-home team
Last week: 3-5; Season: 16-31-1. Plays of the day: 1-5
